ew suspicious of her when she became pregnant shortly after their wedding. To prove her fidelity to her husband, she entered a benign [[Bedroom|bower]] and miraculously gave birth to a son, unscathed by the surrounding flames. The fire ceremony at Fuji-Yyoshida recalls this story as a means of protecting the town from fire and promoting easy childbirth among women."</ref>

